# CTRFHub — example environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # then edit .env with secrets
#
# `.env` is gitignored. `.env.example` is committed and serves as the
# canonical list of expected variables. New variables get a placeholder
# entry here as they're introduced.
#
# For CI / GitHub Actions, secrets go in the repo's Actions secrets
# (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions, or `gh secret set NAME`).

# --- Tugboat ---
# Per-PR preview environments via Tugboat's free tier (see
# docs/planning/tasks.md → CI-003 and docs/planning/project-architecture.md
# checklist item 30). Token from https://dashboard.tugboatqa.com → Account
# → Access Tokens.
#
# Used by future CI-003 work to poll Tugboat's REST API at
# https://api.tugboatqa.com/v3 for preview status and `/health` before
# the CI E2E job ingests its CTRF report. Also useful locally if you want
# to script against the API.
#
# NOT used: your Tugboat account password. Anything programmatic uses the
# token; the password is only for browser login when doing T2.5
# verification against a Tugboat preview.
TUGBOAT_API_TOKEN=

# --- (more variables will land here as INFRA-001 → AUTH-001 → ... ship) ---
# Examples that future stories will introduce:
#   DATABASE_URL=
#   BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=
#   OPENROUTER_API_KEY=     # optional, only if AI_PROVIDER=openai/openrouter
#   AI_PROVIDER=            # 'mock' | 'openai' | 'anthropic' | 'groq'
#   ARTIFACT_STORAGE=       # 'local' | 's3'
#   ARTIFACT_PUBLIC_URL=    # optional, for separate-origin artifact serving
